The search is continuing for the body of a 6-year-old boy who fell into a manhole in Dlamini, Soweto. Khayalethu Magadla was playing with friends when the incident happened on Sunday afternoon. eNCA reporter Pule Letswiti-Jones has more. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The search is continuing on Tuesday for the body of a six-year-old boy who fell into a manhole in Dlamini, Soweto. Khayalethu Magadla was playing with friends when the incident happened on Sunday afternoon. READ: Six-year-old Soweto child falls into open manhole His family has been left reeling. Magadla's father says the family desperately need his body to be found.